Hi !
 trying to reduce memory-trace of 2.2.13 at runtime (image size is 
 not so critical). wondered if there are any projects running to have
 a "minimize" configuration option ? I naively tried reducing
 values in linux/include/tty.h limits.h etc. wich has
 a very small efect on the runtime size of the Kernel (-8K). Any
 hints how to snip of resources ? this is for a 
 minimum real-time-linux system that curently runs in 8MB 
 (4MB-RAM + 4MB-RAMDISK) after bootup 2MB are allready reserved by the kernel.
 details and first versions at
   
http://www.thinkingnerds.com/projects/minirtl/minirtl.html
thx
